      <a name="job1"></a>
      <span class="bodySubtitle">Senior Linux/Kernel/OS Verification Engineer</span>
      <br><br>
      Engineering, San Mateo, CA
      <br><br>
      4+ years of software development experience using C/C++, preferably in Linux Kernel and Operating System development. Knowledge of scripting languages such as UNIX shells, AWK, Perl and Python is essential. Experience in XML, HTML, Web server and database will be a plus. In depth knowledge of Linux Operating System and Kernel is required. Working experience with Windows operating system is desirable. Good understanding of contemporary QA/test principles, methodologies, and techniques in regards to black/white box testing and test automation needed. General knowledge of software and system security is expected. Networking essentials required. Excellent verbal and written communications skills required. Highly driven, positive attitude, team player, self learning, self motivating and flexibility are some of the attributes needed for this position.
      <br><br>
      <strong>Responsibilities:</strong><br>
      This individual will work on challenging software verification and quality assessment assignments with a mission to release high quality system software that is highly resilient and optimally performing on very large networks. The scope of verification will encompass new functionality from release to release, as well as reported defects, using innovative software testing methodologies. Some of the activities will include: developing testing tools, authoring white/black box test cases, creating target test applications, building/using harnesses to test new and existing hardware/software components, participate in requirement, specification, design and code reviews, and automating test cases for repeatability. Working at source code (C/C++) level; this individual shall propose white box test points, implement module level as well as bug-specific directed unit tests and automate unit tests that can be executed on every build. Participate in software maintenance releases, generate test plans, develop quality matrices, execute test plans and produce release documentation.
      <br><br>
      <strong>Education Requirements</strong><br>
      At least BS in Computer Science; MS preferable.
