      Engineering, Cambridge, MA
      <br><br>
      The Nameservers group develops the sophisticated DNS services at the core of the Akamai platform. Akamai DNS provides the critical mechanism that enables intelligent content routing decisions for millions of users and billions of requests on a daily basis.
      <br><br>
      The Nameservers group is looking for a top engineer to develop and extend our DNS software. As a Senior Software Engineer, your responsibilities will include:
      <br><br>
      <ul>
      <li>Full-time software development. </li>
      <li>Designing, developing, and testing DNS server software. </li>
      <li>Maintaining existing systems. </li>
      <li>Experience working in all phases of the software development lifecycle, from requirements gathering to design, implementation, testing, and release. </li>
      </ul>
      <strong>Qualifications:</strong><br>
      <ul>
      <li>MS or higher degree in Computer Science or equivalent. </li>
      <li>5 years experience in C++ and C software development for Unix. </li>
      <li>Substantial experience in network server software. </li>
      <li>Previous DNS server experience a plus. </li>
      <li>Proven track record implementing complex algorithms in real systems. </li>
      <li>Excellent verbal and written communications skills. </li>
      <li>Flexibility to undertake new challenges at a moment's notice.</li>
      </ul>
